verses.roman:
jagat-mohana kṛṣṇa, tāṅhāra mohinī
ataeva samastera parā ṭhākurāṇī

synonyms: jagat-mohana—enchanting the universe; kṛṣṇa—Lord Kṛṣṇa; tāṅhāra—of Him; mohinī—the enchantress; ataeva—therefore; samastera—of all; parā—foremost; ṭhākurāṇī—goddess.
translation: Lord Kṛṣṇa enchants the world, but Śrī Rādhā enchants even Him. Therefore She is the supreme goddess of all.
